[[#excerpt]]
It isn't easy to configure workspaces in the stock Ubuntu 11.10 release. Starting with the article at [[http://pof.eslack.org/2011/10/03/change-workspace-configuration-on-ubuntu-11-10/ | pof.eslack.org]] on this very topic, a comment was given describing how to adjust workspace configuration using [[CompizConfig Settings Manager -> http://wiki.compiz.org/CCSM#Using_CCSM]]
[[#excerptend]]

!! 1. Install CCSM

(:source lang=bash:)
# apt-get install compizconfig-settings-manager
(:sourceend:)

!! 2. Running CCSM

(:source lang=bash:)
$ ccsm 1>/dev/null 2>&1 &
(:sourceend:)

!! 3. Configuring Workspaces

!!! a. Go to General Options:

Attach:GotoGeneralOptions.jpg

!!! b. Click on Desktop Size:

Attach:ClickOnDesktopSize.jpg

!!! c. Select the Horizontal and Vertical Spaces

Attach:SelectHorizontalAndVerticalSpaces.jpg

!!! d. Click "Back"

Attach:ClickBack.jpg

!!! e. Click "Close"

Attach:ClickCloseToSave.jpg

That should do it!



